Class UnionSketch

    public class UnionSketch
extends org.apache.pig.EvalFunc<org.apache.pig.data.DataByteArray>
implements org.apache.pig.Accumulator<org.apache.pig.data.DataByteArray>, org.apache.pig.Algebraic
    This UDF is to merge sketches. This class implements both the Accumulator and Algebraic interfaces for performance optimization.

        public org.apache.pig.data.DataByteArray exec(org.apache.pig.data.Tuple inputTuple)
                                       throws IOException
        Top-level exec function. This method accepts an input Tuple containing a Bag of one or more inner Sketch Tuples and returns a single updated Sketch as a DataByteArray.

        Types are in the form: Java data type: Pig DataType

        Input Tuple

        • Tuple: TUPLE (Must contain only one field)
          • index 0: DataBag: BAG (May contain 0 or more Inner Tuples)
            • index 0: Tuple: TUPLE Sketch Tuple
            • ...
            • index n-1: Tuple: TUPLE Sketch Tuple
        Sketch Tuple
        • Tuple: TUPLE (Contains exactly 1 field)
          • index 0: DataByteArray: BYTEARRAY = The serialization of a Sketch object.

      • accumulate

        public void accumulate(org.apache.pig.data.Tuple inputTuple)
                throws IOException
        An Accumulator version of the standard exec() method. Like exec(), accumulator is called with a bag of Sketch Tuples. Unlike exec(), it doesn't serialize the sketch at the end. Instead, it can be called multiple times, each time with another bag of Sketch Tuples to be input to the Union.
        Specified by:
        accumulate in interface org.apache.pig.Accumulator<org.apache.pig.data.DataByteArray>
        Parameters:
        inputTuple - A tuple containing a single bag, containing Sketch Tuples.
        Throws:
        IOException - by Pig
